manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Features and Benefits More Lubrication. Less Irritation. Lubricating strip, with Vitamin E, to help reduce skin irritation. Sensitive Skin Sensitive skin formula, to shave your every curve. 5 Blades. 1 Close Shave. Double coated blade edge for a close shave.

Frequently Asked Questions Q: Will Solimo razor blade refills fit my other existing handles? A: No, Solimo blade refills fit Solimo handles only. Q: Is there a lot of lubrication on this razor? A: Yes, our Solimo 5-blade razor has a blue lubrication strip surrounding the blades that when activated by water, releases botanical oils to help the razor glide over the skin for a smooth shave. Q: Is this razor suited for sensitive skin? A: Yes, the Solimo 5-blade razor has a lubricating strip with Vitamin E to help reduce irritation, has been dermatologically tested and is hypoallergenic. Q: How long does each razor head last? A: This is different for each person and depends on usage and hair type, but a good indication to change the blades is when shaving is not close or tugs on hairs.

Instructions for How To Load and Change Cartridge For Loading Cartridge onto Handle: Remove handle from tray. Remove one cartridge pod from tray. Hold the larger half of cartridge pod with the blades of cartridge facing down, remove plastic top. Push razor handle into the back of the cartridge until it clicks. Remove bottom half of plastic pod from cartridge to expose the blades. You are ready to shave! For Changing Cartridge: Push razor handle button forward to release cartridge. Then load new cartridge.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've only had to buy 2 refill packs of 5 since I bought the razor in 2021. Second pack still has 4 cartridges. Lasts longer than any razor I've ever owned in over 30 years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great razor for the value!
reviews.reviewText: I don't write a lot of product reviews but I had to come on here to leave on for this razor. I was extremely hesitant on purchasing this razor. Being cheaper than the others and I've always used the Venus Razor. Well I'm here to let you know, do it. It's an actually really really good razor! Best part is that the blades and the moisture strip stay good for a good amount of time too! Then you get like 12 extra blades. I've had mine since the end of October and now it's just after Christmas. I have only been through about 3 blades since purchasing. The moisture strip does get a little gooey but it's worth it IMO. Can't beat the price now days with everything being so overpriced. Give it a try!Also , I personally haven't had any issues with irritation. My skin is somewhat sensitive but I've used it everywhere (yes down there) and not had any problems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best razor for legs ever
reviews.reviewText: Works better than Venus and all other razors I’ve tried, including men’s five blades for legs. You do not have to use a lot of shaving cream or anything, the blades are protected nicely with a sensitive softener (not sure how to describe). Nice find!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A bit bulky but good
reviews.reviewText: These razors are a good, affordable razor option. They are comfortable to use and I like them for leg and pit shaving. I find them a bit bulky to do a good job on the bikini area but fine for the other areas I mentioned. I would buy again. I just need fewer blades for bikini shaving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Been using over a year now and I really like the razor. I had been using a subscription brand and this one is just as good.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Impressed with the quality
reviews.reviewText: Excellent value for money and very good razor I’m seriously impressed

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good for beginners- not a close shave
reviews.reviewText: I'd recommend this as a first razor for shaving your body! It's very safe compared to other razors. You'll still want lotion once you finish, but it's not super irritating.Personally, I'm going back to dollar shave club. It's not a close shave at all. I'm talking at least a 2 day difference between this and a more traditional razor. The hydrating strip only leaves gel behind after you shave, so I really don't understand the point of it. The gel does not act like a lotion.I've used a unisex razor for as long as I can remember, but I thought I'd try something girly after I ran out of blades. I never understood the benefit of a women's razor and I still don't. It just has more plastic and some gunk.Pro-tip: apply baby oil immediately after shaving while in the shower. It will help seal in hydration until you get out and use lotion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love these! I had been using Harry’s razors, but these, I believe, are actually better quality and definitely much cheaper!

reviews.reviewTitle: My wife prefers the Solimo men's razors I buy
reviews.reviewText: When Amazon launched Solimo razors, I decided to buy some of the men's ones for myself and this women's one for my wife. Since I bought a large pack with 16 cartridges, I offered my wife to try out the men's one after using this women's version and she preferred the men's one more, especially when she found out the men's ones were cheaper. Since we both switched to Solimo men's razors, I discovered that the exact same handles and cartridges are sold at FreshCo/Sobeys/Foodland under the store brand, and they're even cheaper than the Solimo cartridges, so we'll be buying from there in the future.

I ordered this razor after reading all the reviews on it and decided that it was worth a try. I have always had trouble finding the right razor that didn't leave little cuts around my knees, but this one worked so well! I now have the refills sent to every other month! Definitely give this a try.

Bought it. Tried it. It was okay for 3 shaves but useless afterwards. Even when new, it doesn’t come close to Venus. I will go back to buying expensive Venus because it cost less when the blade lasts longer, Duh! Will I buy this again? Maybe, if Venus becomes so expensive I can’t cough up the money.

I have been looking for a good quality razor with 5 blades. So far I haven't found anything that gives a nice close shave, until now. The head swivels to go around curves, and has something in the head that moisturizes as you shave. So far it seems to give a nice close shave, but I haven't used it long enough to know how long it lasts.

I like this just fine. Does what you want it to do. The moisturizing strip works well. I’m disappointed that the refills are touch and go as for availability. Well worth the money if you can get the 12 pack refills.
